  "headline": "Film History",
  "description": "Film evolved from still photography and persistence of vision experiments. Lumière brothers' first public screening (1895, Paris) is considered cinema's birth. Silent era (1895-1927), Golden Age of Hollywood (1930s-50s), New Wave movements (1950s-70s), Blockbuster era (1975+), digital cinema (2000+).",
